{"timestamp":"1687025579","author":"vabold","description":"In its current state, this isn't really an improvement.\r\n\r\nIn my view, a good error message should strive to do three things:\r\n1) Inform the user in a way anyone can understand about what the problem is.\r\n2) Explain what the user might have done that could have caused it.\r\n3) Provide steps on how to potentially fix the problem.\r\n\r\nIt's true that end users likely do not know what `main.dol` and `StaticR.rel` are, but for people who aren't familiar with Wii game patching, this still doesn't provide a lot of help."}
